15/06/2004
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Violent storms have hit Romania since the weekend, causing significant damage in some areas and reportedly killing a child in the northern town of Doljesti.
Local media reports Monday (14 June) said a two-year-old was swept away by floodwaters and torrents of mud.
A number of houses and electricity infrastructure facilities were damaged or destroyed, along with huge areas of farmland.
Meteorologists say the severe weather may continue through the week.
(AFP, Mediafax - 14/06/04)
